 california division of juvenile justice djj by the conclusion of this course students should have an understanding of the juvenile justice system and how it compares with the adult justice system what programs work to reduce recidivism and be cognizant of some of the major legal and policy issues confronting that system today number of units 3 course number 527 recently taught by joan petersilia related links axess coursework digital reserve sls registrar related stanford criminal justice center scjc cloudy 56 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
